User-Defined Functions (UDFs) allow you to create custom functions in PySpark. You can apply these functions to
your DataFrame columns.
Example:
from pyspark.sql.functions import udf
def multiply_by_two(x):
return x * 2
multiply_udf = udf(multiply_by_two)
df.withColumn("new_col", multiply_udf(df["existing_col"])).show()
